quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,152,"Verily as to those who took the calf as a god, wrath from their Lord shall overtake them, and shame in this present life: for thus recompense we the devisers of a lie"
  7,153,"But to those who have done evil, then afterwards repent and believe, thy Lord will thereafter be Lenient, Merciful"
  7,154,"And when the anger of Moses was stilled, he took up the tables; and in their writing was guidance and mercy for those who dread their Lord"
  7,155,"And Moses chose seventy men of his people for a meeting appointed by us. And when the earthquake overtook them, he said, \"O my Lord! if it had been thy pleasure, thou hadst destroyed them and me ere this! wilt thou destroy us for what our foolish ones have done? It is nought but thy trial: thou wilt mislead by it whom thou wilt, and guide whom thou wilt. Our guardian, thou! Forgive us then and have mercy on us; for of those who forgive art thou the best"
  7,156,"And write down for us what is good in this world, as well as in the world to come, for to thee are we guided.\" He said, \"My chastisement shall fall on whom I will, and my mercy embraceth all things, and I write it down for those who shall fear me, and pay the alms, and believe in our signs"
  7,157,"Who shall follow the Apostle, the unlettered Prophet - whom they shall find described with them in the Law and Evangel. What is right will he enjoin them, and forbid them what is wrong, and will allow them healthful viands and prohibit the impure, and will ease them of their burden, and of the yokes which were upon them; and those who shall believe in him, and strengthen him, and help him, and follow the light which hath been sent down with him, - these are they with whom it shall be well"